 <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0033.tlg002.perseus-grc1:3:23\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Id.\">Id.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ P.\">P.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">3.23</biblScope> </bibl> </cit>; <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">τὰ δ᾽ οὐκ ἄρ᾽ ἔμελλε θεὸς μ. θήσειν</quote_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0005.tlg001.perseus-grc1:22:181\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Theoc.\">Theoc.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">22.181</biblScope></bibl></cit>. —Used by <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Hom.</author> </bibl> only in neut. pl.: the etym. is dub., cf. <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">μωνιή, μωνιόν</foreign>; but later Poets apptly. connected the word with <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ἄνεμος</foreign> (as if for <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">μετανεμώνιος</foreign>)<foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">; κονία μεταμώνιος ἀέρθη</foreign> <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">borne by the wind, on high</tr_>, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0261.tlg001:16\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Simon.</author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">16</biblScope> </bibl>; <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">ἐς κόρακας βαδιεῖ μεταμώνιος</quote_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0019.tlg005.perseus-grc1:117\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Ar.\">Ar.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Pax\">Pax</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">117</biblScope></bibl></cit>, ubi <abbr TEIform=\"abbr\">v.</abbr> Sch.:— <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">μεταμώλιος</foreign> is <abbr TEIform=\"abbr\">v.l. in</abbr> several passages; cf. <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEI